This magnificent beach house in Beachy Head Drive, one of Plett’s most prestigious streets, boasts luxurious living areas with ceiling-to-floor sliding doors leading to an expansive outdoor entertainment area and pool. The house has three bedrooms, two guest suites as well as a flat. Other features include a teen pad/games room, study, staff accommodation, a stand-by generator, garaging for three cars and quick beach access. Plots in Nooitgedacht, a new gated estate launched off-plan last week in the tranquil harbour village, are priced from R2.95m while plot-and-plan packages are available from R7.4m. The estate offers residents a secure, upmarket lifestyle in a scenic, natural setting. Nooitgedacht comprises 20 stands sized from 946m² to 1,400m².